N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 135.1 - Definitions

State Regulations

As used in these regulations the following terms shall
mean: (a) Blossom thinning sprays. A
spray used on fruit trees when said trees are in blossom, which spray has a
tendency to kill a part of the blossoms. Notes
